"Hazy golden yellow covered with a nice looking head of sticky creaminess. Smells like a pleasant blend of herbs and flowers on top of a biscuity pale malt base. Lavender, cardamom, coriander, honey, flower petals, licorice, and sugary citrus...spiced up and adorned like many American Saisons tend to be, but Stone pulls of the blend very well. Flavor opens up with a blast of spicy yeast, leading to a more subtle lavender and herb presence, and finishing quite crisp and dry. Zesty citrus, perfumey floral notes, peppercorns, grass. and mint. Definitely not a Saison where the yeast and funk do all the talking - again, more of a jazzed-up American style, which I'm generally not a huge fan of, but I like the end result here. It's a fun, pleasant, tasty blend of flavors that I found quite enjoyable."
