"Had on tap today at Sticks and Stones.Came to the table ina snifter a light lemon yellow with a half finger white head that left some froth.Lemon oils in the nose along with some yeasty spice.Tart lemon flavors with the sage just faintly is detected,mild white pepper in the finish.Not but it's not overly complex,basic but drinkable."
"As a long time fan of Stone I was excited to try their take on the saison. Picked up a sixer for a memorial day bbq. This one pours a hazy straw color with a small and short lasting white head that leaves little lacing. The nose is a refreshing blend of citrus (lemon peel and oranges), spices (coriander, pepper, and juniper, and bready malt and funky yeast. Its quite a nice bouquet. The mouthfeel is light, effervescent, and quenching. The taste is not quite as refreshing as the nose with more west coast hops dominating and not as much of the belgian and farmhouse characteristics coming through. It is still a nice blend of citrus, spice, and funkiness though. This was good but I was hoping for more from such a great brewer. Uts definitely a Stone style saison though."
""
"12 oz bottle. Pours hazy golden with small, short-lived, white head. Aroma is of funky yeast, spices, bready malt, wheat and some floral hops. Body is medium and tangy. Herbal hops, funky yeast, pale malt and lemon zest fill the mouth. Finish is long, dry and spicy. Nice brew for spicy foods."
