"Overall I thought this was a decent beer and a pretty average example of the style, it had most of the aspects that I look for in the style, but they weren't as refined as I would like them to be and that made this beer feel a little rough around the edges and the balance seemed to be a little out of wack. This beer didn't have the best drinkability, it was fairly smooth, not the cleanest, slightly crisp, not too filling and the taste didn't do the best job at holding my attention so one would be enough for me, I don't have any urge to drink another one in a row. What I liked the most about this beer was the appearance, I thought it was pretty good and it seemed to be the aspect that was truest to style. What I liked the least about this beer was the balance and the lower amount of carbonation, to me those were things that needed the most work. I wouldn't get this beer again, it's pretty easy to find a Saison that better suites my taste and I don't think I would recommend this as a good Saison. All in all I wasn't too impressed with this beer, lately I've found myself being a little let down with these new beers from Stone and this one is no different. It's for sure not my favorite Saison and it's not even close to being one of the better beers from Stone. I appreciate the effort, but this one could use some work, better luck next time guys."
